{
  "texts": [
    "The quality factor of the DCZ oscillation is well above 100 at T = 0.1 K and remains at least 50 above 1 K, exhibiting a coherence reduction similar to that in T 2 Hahn (Fig. 4a).",
    "See Extended Data Fig. 8 for the full characterization of exchange.",
    "We assess the DCZ gate metrics using two-qubit interleaved randomized benchmarking (IRB) 50 and fast Bayesian tomography (FBT) 53 (Methods), which report DCZ fidelities of 99.8 ± 0.2%, 99.15 ± 0.13% at T = 0.1 K, and 97.7 ± 1.5%, 98.92 ± 0.67% at T = 1 K. In Fig. 4c, we show the five largest components from Hamiltonian error and stochastic error obtained from FBT.",
    "Going from 0.1 K to 1 K, we see a change in the error landscape.",
    "At both temperatures, exchange noise appears as one of the main noise sources."
  ]
}